---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="proof"
  description="n0brains live forward-return proof — every signal type measured against real post-signal price action, with win rate, excess vs BTC, and confidence intervals. The exact gate we use to flag signals. Not advice."
  ogImage="/og-proof.png"
>
  <section class="proof-page">
    <div class="section-label" data-reveal="fade">live audit · refreshed every 60s</div>
    <h1 class="proof-h1">
      <span class="hl"><span class="hli">WE PUBLISH</span></span>
      <span class="hl"><span class="hli accent">OUR WIN-RATE.</span></span>
    </h1>
    <p class="proof-lede">
      Most of the industry sells backtests you can't audit. We measure
      <strong>every directional signal</strong> against real post-signal prices
      and publish the result live — wins, losses, and the types we demote.
      This page renders the <em>exact</em> gate the pipeline uses to flag
      <code>conviction: strong</code>, so it can never claim edge the product
      doesn't actually act on.
    </p>

    <!-- Live stat band — every number from the same /proof endpoint -->
    <div class="stat-band" id="stat-band">
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-num" id="st-proven">–</span>
        <span class="stat-label">proven signal types</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-num" id="st-signals">–</span>
        <span class="stat-label">signals measured · 30d</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-num" id="st-best">–</span>
        <span class="stat-label">best proven win-rate</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat-num">24h</span>
        <span class="stat-label">horizon · real HL prices</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="proof-banner" class="proof-banner proof-loading">
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span class="banner-text">loading results…</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Proven types — the headline numbers -->
    <div class="proven-cards" id="proven-cards" aria-live="polite"></div>

    <h2 class="proof-h2">The full audit — failures included</h2>
    <p class="proof-sub">
      Types that don't clear the bar stay on the board as <em>intel only</em>.
      Public demotion is the feature: when edge decays, this table says so
      before our marketing does.
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrap" id="proof-table"></div>
    <p class="meta" id="proof-meta"></p>

    <!-- Methodology — the fine print, in the open -->
    <div class="method-panel">
      <div class="method-head">methodology</div>
      <p>
        Every directional signal is measured against real post-signal price
        action — Hyperliquid 1-hour candles — at the 24h horizon over a rolling
        30-day window. For each signal type we publish the win rate, the mean
        return of the trade itself, the mean <strong>excess vs BTC over the
        same window</strong>, and 95% confidence intervals. A type is marked
        <strong>proven</strong> only when it clears 30+ measured signals AND
        both beats BTC AND is profitable on its own (excess-return CI lower
        bound above zero). Beating BTC alone isn't enough — a type that only
        looks good by being short in a downtrend, while still losing money,
        does not qualify. The live <code>trade_signal</code> gate applies this
        same test per (type, direction) and is regime-aware.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="proof-h2">Edge accumulation</h2>
    <p class="proof-sub">
      Does the per-signal edge above actually compound, or is it a few lucky
      outliers? Below is an illustrative account starting at index 100 that takes
      <strong>every proven-type signal</strong>, one at a time, risking
      <span id="eq-alloc">1%</span> of equity per signal and compounding the
      realized 24h return — in fire-time order. Fixed fractional size, no
      leverage, no stacking. <strong>Illustrative of edge accumulation on measured
      returns, not a live-traded or guaranteed account.</strong>
    </p>
    <div id="equity-wrap">
      <div id="equity-legend" class="equity-legend"></div>
      <div id="equity-chart" class="equity-chart">loading…</div>
    </div>
    <p class="meta" id="equity-meta"></p>

    <p class="legal-updated" style="margin-top: 32px;">
      A type is shown as <strong>forward-return proven</strong> only when its
      live post-signal price record clears 30+ measured signals AND both beats
      BTC and is profitable on its own, with a 95% confidence interval
      above zero. These are the types we flag <code>conviction: strong</code>
      in the API. Measured on real prices for informational purposes only — not
      financial advice, and past performance does not guarantee future results.
      See <a href="/terms">terms</a>.
    </p>

    <!-- Conversion path -->
    <div class="proof-cta" data-reveal>
      <h3>These numbers update whether they flatter us or not.</h3>
      <p>Pipe the proven signals straight into your agent — REST, WebSocket, Webhook, MCP, or x402.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-primary">Start Free →</a>
        <a href="/docs/" class="btn btn-secondary">API Docs ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const ENDPOINT = "https://api.n0brains.com/proof";
  const REDUCE = window.matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches;
  let countedUp = false;

  function pct(v) {
    if (v === null || v === undefined) return "—";
    const n = Number(v) * 100;
    return n.toFixed(1) + "%";
  }
  function pctRaw(v) {
    if (v === null || v === undefined) return "—";
    return (Number(v) >= 0 ? "+" : "") + Number(v).toFixed(2) + "%";
  }

  function countUp(el, target, fmt, dur = 900) {
    if (REDUCE) { el.textContent = fmt(target); return; }
    const t0 = performance.now();
    const tick = (now) => {
      const p = Math.min((now - t0) / dur, 1);
      const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - p, 3);
      el.textContent = fmt(target * eased);
      if (p < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
    };
    requestAnimationFrame(tick);
  }

  function renderStats(data) {
    const proven = data.types.filter((t) => t.tradeable);
    const totalN = data.types.reduce((a, t) => a + (t.n || 0), 0);
    const best = proven.length ? Math.max(...proven.map((t) => t.win_rate || 0)) : null;
    const stP = document.getElementById("st-proven");
    const stS = document.getElementById("st-signals");
    const stB = document.getElementById("st-best");
    if (countedUp) {
      // Subsequent refreshes: update silently, no re-animation.
      stP.textContent = String(proven.length);
      stS.textContent = totalN.toLocaleString();
      stB.textContent = best === null ? "—" : (best * 100).toFixed(1) + "%";
      return;
    }
    countedUp = true;
    countUp(stP, proven.length, (v) => Math.round(v).toString());
    countUp(stS, totalN, (v) => Math.round(v).toLocaleString());
    if (best === null) stB.textContent = "—";
    else countUp(stB, best * 100, (v) => v.toFixed(1) + "%");
  }

  function renderProvenCards(data) {
    const wrap = document.getElementById("proven-cards");
    const proven = data.types
      .filter((t) => t.tradeable)
      .sort((a, b) => (b.excess_pct || 0) - (a.excess_pct || 0));
    if (!proven.length) {
      wrap.innerHTML = `<div class="pv-empty">0 types currently clear the bar.
        The gate is real — when edge decays, this page says so first.</div>`;
      return;
    }
    wrap.innerHTML = proven.map((t, i) => `
      <div class="pv-card" style="--pvi:${i}">
        <div class="pv-head">
          <span class="pv-type">${t.signal_type}</span>
          <span class="badge badge-yes">proven</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pv-win">${pct(t.win_rate)}<span>win rate · n=${t.n}</span></div>
        <div class="pv-rows">
          <div><span>avg return</span><b class="${t.avg_net_pct >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.avg_net_pct)}</b></div>
          <div><span>excess vs BTC</span><b class="${t.excess_pct >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.excess_pct)}</b></div>
          <div><span>95% CI low</span><b class="${t.ci_low_pct > 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.ci_low_pct)}</b></div>
        </div>
      </div>`).join("");
  }

  function render(data) {
    const banner = document.getElementById("proof-banner");
    const table  = document.getElementById("proof-table");
    const meta   = document.getElementById("proof-meta");

    if (!data || data.error || !data.types) {
      banner.className = "proof-banner proof-unknown";
      banner.querySelector(".banner-text").textContent =
        "proof unavailable (" + (data?.error || "fetch failed") + ")";
      return;
    }

    renderStats(data);
    renderProvenCards(data);

    const tradeable = data.types.filter((t) => t.tradeable);
    banner.className = "proof-banner proof-up";
    banner.querySelector(".banner-text").textContent =
      tradeable.length + " signal type" + (tradeable.length === 1 ? "" : "s") +
      " forward-return proven";

    let rows = "";
    for (const t of data.types) {
      const cls = t.tradeable ? "row-tradeable" : "row-untradeable";
      const flag = t.tradeable
        ? '<span class="badge badge-yes">proven</span>'
        : '<span class="badge badge-no">intel only</span>';
      // CI shown as the lower bound on excess return — the conservative edge.
      const ciCls = t.ci_low_pct > 0 ? "pos" : "neg";
      rows += `
        <tr class="${cls}">
          <td class="type">${t.signal_type}</td>
          <td>${t.n}</td>
          <td>${pct(t.win_rate)}</td>
          <td class="${t.avg_net_pct >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.avg_net_pct)}</td>
          <td class="${t.excess_pct >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.excess_pct)}</td>
          <td class="${ciCls}">${pctRaw(t.ci_low_pct)}</td>
          <td>${flag}</td>
        </tr>`;
    }
    table.innerHTML = `
      <table class="proof-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>type</th><th>signals</th><th>win rate</th>
              <th title="mean return of the trade itself">avg return</th>
              <th title="mean return minus BTC over the same window">excess vs BTC</th>
              <th title="95% confidence lower bound on excess return — the conservative edge">excess CI low</th>
              <th></th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>${rows}</tbody>
      </table>`;

    if (data.types[0] && data.types[0].updated_at) {
      const latest = Math.max(...data.types.map((t) => t.updated_at || 0));
      meta.textContent = "Last updated " + new Date(latest * 1000).toISOString();
    }
  }

  async function load() {
    try {
      const r = await fetch(ENDPOINT, { cache: "no-store" });
      render(await r.json());
    } catch (e) {
      render({ error: String(e) });
    }
  }

  load();
  setInterval(load, 60_000);

  // ── Equity curve (illustrative edge accumulation) ──────────────────
  const EQUITY_ENDPOINT = "https://api.n0brains.com/proof/equity";
  const TYPE_COLORS = ["#4ade80", "#60a5fa", "#f59e0b", "#c084fc", "#f472b6"];

  function buildPath(points, x0, y0, w, h, tMin, tMax, eqMin, eqMax) {
    if (!points.length) return "";
    const sx = (t) => x0 + ((t - tMin) / (tMax - tMin || 1)) * w;
    const sy = (e) => y0 + h - ((e - eqMin) / (eqMax - eqMin || 1)) * h;
    // Downsample to ~300 points so the SVG path stays light.
    const step = Math.max(1, Math.floor(points.length / 300));
    let d = "";
    for (let i = 0; i < points.length; i += step) {
      const p = points[i];
      d += (d ? "L" : "M") + sx(p.t).toFixed(1) + "," + sy(p.equity).toFixed(1) + " ";
    }
    const last = points[points.length - 1];
    d += "L" + sx(last.t).toFixed(1) + "," + sy(last.equity).toFixed(1);
    return d;
  }

  function renderEquity(d) {
    const chart = document.getElementById("equity-chart");
    const legend = document.getElementById("equity-legend");
    const meta = document.getElementById("equity-meta");
    const allocEl = document.getElementById("eq-alloc");
    if (!d || d.error || !d.combined || !d.combined.length) {
      chart.innerHTML = "<div class='tier-err'>equity curve unavailable</div>";
      return;
    }
    if (allocEl && d.alloc_frac_per_signal != null) {
      allocEl.textContent = (d.alloc_frac_per_signal * 100).toFixed(d.alloc_frac_per_signal < 0.01 ? 1 : 0) + "%";
    }

    const W = 720, H = 300, padL = 48, padR = 16, padT = 16, padB = 28;
    const w = W - padL - padR, h = H - padT - padB;

    // Series: combined + each proven type. "All proven" gets a bright, thick
    // white line so it reads as the headline series vs the thinner per-type lines.
    const COMBINED_COLOR = "#ffffff";
    const series = [{ name: "All proven (combined)", points: d.combined, color: COMBINED_COLOR, width: 2.6 }];
    const types = Object.keys(d.by_type || {});
    types.forEach((t, i) => {
      series.push({ name: t, points: d.by_type[t], color: TYPE_COLORS[i % TYPE_COLORS.length], width: 1.6 });
    });

    let tMin = Infinity, tMax = -Infinity, eqMin = Infinity, eqMax = -Infinity;
    for (const s of series) for (const p of s.points) {
      if (p.t < tMin) tMin = p.t; if (p.t > tMax) tMax = p.t;
      if (p.equity < eqMin) eqMin = p.equity; if (p.equity > eqMax) eqMax = p.equity;
    }
    // Pad the y-range a touch and always include the 100 baseline.
    eqMin = Math.min(eqMin, 100); eqMax = Math.max(eqMax, 100);
    const yPad = (eqMax - eqMin) * 0.08 || 1; eqMin -= yPad; eqMax += yPad;

    const yBase = padT + h - ((100 - eqMin) / (eqMax - eqMin || 1)) * h;
    const gridVals = [eqMin, (eqMin + eqMax) / 2, eqMax];
    let grid = "";
    for (const gv of gridVals) {
      const gy = padT + h - ((gv - eqMin) / (eqMax - eqMin || 1)) * h;
      grid += `<line x1="${padL}" y1="${gy.toFixed(1)}" x2="${W - padR}" y2="${gy.toFixed(1)}" class="eq-grid"/>`;
      grid += `<text x="${padL - 6}" y="${(gy + 3).toFixed(1)}" class="eq-axis" text-anchor="end">${gv.toFixed(0)}</text>`;
    }

    let paths = "";
    for (const s of series) {
      const dPath = buildPath(s.points, padL, padT, w, h, tMin, tMax, eqMin, eqMax);
      paths += `<path d="${dPath}" fill="none" stroke="${s.color}" stroke-width="${s.width}"/>`;
    }

    chart.innerHTML = `
      <svg viewBox="0 0 ${W} ${H}" class="eq-svg" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
        ${grid}
        <line x1="${padL}" y1="${yBase.toFixed(1)}" x2="${W - padR}" y2="${yBase.toFixed(1)}" class="eq-base"/>
        ${paths}
      </svg>`;

    // Legend built straight from `series` so colors + labels always match the
    // chart lines exactly. Swatch is a short line segment (matching the drawn
    // line), not a square, so "this color = this line" is unambiguous. Each
    // entry shows the series' final return.
    const byRet = d.by_type_return_pct || {};
    const retFor = (s) => s.name.startsWith("All proven")
      ? d.combined_return_pct
      : byRet[s.name];
    legend.innerHTML =
      `<span class="eq-leg-title">Lines</span>` +
      series.map((s) => {
        const r = retFor(s);
        const rv = (r === null || r === undefined) ? "" :
          `<b class="${r >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(r)}</b>`;
        // Fully inline the swatch styles: this span is injected via innerHTML, so
        // Astro's SCOPED CSS (.eq-swatch[data-astro-cid-…]) never matches it —
        // the dimensions/border must live on the element itself, not in <style>.
        const sw = `display:inline-block;width:14px;height:14px;border-radius:3px;`
          + `flex:0 0 auto;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);background:${s.color};`;
        return `<span class="eq-leg-item">` +
          `<span class="eq-swatch" style="${sw}"></span>` +
          `<span class="eq-leg-name">${s.name}</span>${rv}</span>`;
      }).join("");

    if (meta) {
      meta.textContent =
        `${d.n_signals} proven signals over ${d.window_days} days (~${d.signals_per_day}/day) · ` +
        `index 100 → ${d.combined_final_index} · ${d.alloc_frac_per_signal != null ? (d.alloc_frac_per_signal * 100).toFixed(d.alloc_frac_per_signal < 0.01 ? 1 : 0) + "% per signal" : ""} · ` +
        `illustrative, not a live account`;
    }
  }

  async function loadEquity() {
    try {
      const r = await fetch(EQUITY_ENDPOINT, { cache: "no-store" });
      renderEquity(await r.json());
    } catch (e) {
      renderEquity({ error: String(e) });
    }
  }
  loadEquity();
  setInterval(loadEquity, 120_000);
</script>

<style>
  .proof-page { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .proof-h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
    font-weight: 400; line-height: 0.95; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .proof-h1 .hl { display: block; overflow: hidden; padding-bottom: 0.05em; }
  .proof-h1 .hli {
    display: block; transform: translateY(110%);
    animation: proofLineUp 0.8s var(--ease-out) forwards;
  }
  .proof-h1 .hl:nth-child(2) .hli { animation-delay: 0.14s; }
  @keyframes proofLineUp { to { transform: translateY(0); } }
  .proof-h1 .accent { color: var(--accent); text-shadow: 0 0 36px var(--accent-glow-strong); }

  .proof-lede {
    font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text); max-width: 640px;
    line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);
    animation: fadeUp 0.6s var(--ease-out) 0.35s forwards;
  }
  .proof-lede strong { color: var(--text-heading); }

  /* Live stat band */
  .stat-band {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    opacity: 0; animation: fadeUp 0.6s var(--ease-out) 0.5s forwards;
  }
  .stat { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem 1rem; }
  .stat-num {
    display: block; font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.6rem); line-height: 1;
    color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .stat-label {
    display: block; margin-top: 0.35rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .stat-band { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }

  .proof-banner {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem; border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .proof-banner .dot {
    width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .proof-up { border-color: #2a7a2a; }
  .proof-up .dot { background: #4ade80; box-shadow: 0 0 6px #4ade80; }
  .proof-unknown { border-color: var(--border); }
  .proof-loading .dot { background: var(--accent); }

  /* Proven type cards — JS-injected, style with :global */
  .proven-cards {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { .proven-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  :global(.pv-card) {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-accent); border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--bg-card); padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem;
    box-shadow: 0 0 36px -18px var(--accent-glow-strong);
    opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px);
    animation: fadeUp 0.6s var(--ease-out) calc(0.1s + var(--pvi, 0) * 0.12s) forwards;
  }
  :global(.pv-head) {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  :global(.pv-type) {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--text-heading);
  }
  :global(.pv-win) {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1;
    color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }
  :global(.pv-win span) {
    display: block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }
  :global(.pv-rows > div) {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.78rem;
    padding: 0.3rem 0; border-top: 1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  }
  :global(.pv-rows span) { color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  :global(.pv-rows .pos) { color: #4ade80; }
  :global(.pv-rows .neg) { color: #ef4444; }
  :global(.pv-empty) {
    grid-column: 1 / -1; border: 1px dashed var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted); text-align: center;
  }

  .proof-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--text-heading); margin: 2.5rem 0 0.4rem;
  }
  .proof-sub { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

  /* Full audit table — horizontal scroll on phones */
  .table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
  :global(.proof-table) {
    width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.88rem; min-width: 640px;
  }
  :global(.proof-table th), :global(.proof-table td) {
    padding: 10px 12px; text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  :global(.proof-table th) { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500; }
  :global(.proof-table td.type) { font-weight: 600; }
  :global(.proof-table .pos) { color: #4ade80; }
  :global(.proof-table .neg) { color: #ef4444; }
  :global(.proof-table tbody tr) { transition: background 0.15s ease; }
  :global(.proof-table tbody tr:hover) { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
  :global(.row-untradeable) { opacity: 0.55; }

  :global(.badge) {
    font-size: 0.72rem; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  :global(.badge-yes) { color: #4ade80; border-color: #2a7a2a; }
  :global(.badge-no)  { color: var(--text-muted); }

